        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          We can combine pet hair removal with other services like vacuuming or odor treatment for better value.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">How Do You Remove Pet Hair from Car Seats?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong>We use a multi-step process combining rubber brush extraction, crevice tools, commercial vacuuming, and lint roller finishing to completely remove dog and cat hair from car interiors.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          Standard vacuuming only gets surface-level hair. The barbed structure of pet hair means it hooks into fabric weave and resists suction. Our rubber brushes generate static that lifts embedded hair out of the fibers, making it possible to vacuum away completely.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          This is the same technique used by professional detailers across the country—it works on all fabric types including cloth seats, carpeting, and headliners.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">How Long Does Pet Hair Removal Take?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong>Pet hair removal takes 30 to 45 minutes for most vehicles, depending on hair volume and how deeply it's embedded.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          We don't rush this service. Pet hair removal requires patience and the right technique. Going too fast means leaving hair behind. We work methodically through seats, carpets, door panels, and all the crevices where hair collects.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Your car is ready to drive immediately after we finish.
        </p>
      </section>

